section.section:
A peer reviewer shall:
Be Board certified;
Have special qualifications to judge the matter at hand;
Have received a specified amount of medical experience and training;
Have no formal actions against the peer reviewer's own license;
Receive training in peer review;
Have a standard format for peer review reports; and
To the extent practicable, be licensed and engaged in the practice of medicine in the State.

Services that may be contracted for under this subsection include the services of:
Investigators;
Attorneys;
Accountants;
Expert witnesses;
Consultants; and
Mediators.
